# 詞: 銀包

1. 我成日出門都會將銀包塞係背包側袋，慣咗唔想放褲頭袋。 (I always put my wallet in the side pocket of my backpack when going out, I'm used to not putting it in my front pants pocket.)  
2. 銀包入面除咗現金，仲塞咗幾張積分卡同埋一張舊學生證，雜雜哋嘅。 (Besides cash, there are also a few points cards and an old student ID in the wallet, it's all messy.)  
3. 佢話昨日喺茶餐廳食飯，轉身拿飲料時就掛住銀包，等醒覺已經唔見咗。 (He said he was having tea at a restaurant yesterday, turned around to get a drink and forgot his wallet, by the time he realized it was already gone.)  
4. 阿姐新買嘅銀包係皮製嘅，鏡面鏈條款，成日出門都要鏡下先肯走。 (My sister's new wallet is leather, with a mirror chain design, she always has to check it in the mirror before going out.)  
5. 我個銀包舊咗，拉鏈都有啲卡唔緊，諗住聖誕節叫老豆買新嘅賞賜。 (My wallet is old, the zipper is a bit stuck, I'm thinking of asking Dad to buy a new one as a Christmas gift.)  
6. 買電影票時先發現銀包裏面錢唔夠，唯有開手機支付，險些兒唔夠錢。 (I only found out there wasn't enough money in my wallet when buying movie tickets, so I had to use mobile payment, almost couldn't afford it.)  
7. 個細路仔玩遊戲機時，將媽媽嘅銀包當成道具亂拋，險些兒跌落地板捽爛。 (The little kid was playing with the game console and threw his mom's wallet around as a prop, almost dropping it on the floor and breaking it.)  
8. 同事問我借銀包搭的士，話家裏遺漏咗門匙，要趕緊去開門先。 (My colleague asked to borrow my wallet to take a taxi, saying he left his keys at home and needed to hurry to open the door.)  
9. 警察叔叔幫阿婆找回銀包，裏面有千幾蚊同身份證，阿婆激動到流淚。 (The police uncle helped Grandma find her wallet, which had over a thousand dollars and an ID card inside, Grandma was so touched she cried.)  
